OL,3,C111-year-old crowned world's oldest man
OL,5,FA man from Merseyside has been crowned
OL,6,Fthe world's oldest living man.
OL,8,FJohn Tinniswood was paid a "surprise
OL,9,Fvisit" by the Guinness World Records
OL,10,Fafter the 111-year-old was given the
OL,11,Ftitle after the death of the previous
OL,12,Frecipient.
OL,14,FJuan Vicente Perez, from Venezuela,
OL,15,Fwas confirmed as the world's oldest
OL,16,Fliving man in February 2022 - but he
OL,17,Fdied aged 114 on 2 April.
OL,19,FAs a result John is now officially the
OL,20,Foldest man in the world, aged 111
OL,21,Fyears and 222 days.
